PISA 2012¶

by Sanatbek Matlatipov¶

Investigation Overview¶

I want to investigate how students' life and study has impact on their academic performance as well as conclude those performace.

Dataset Overview¶

PISA is a survey of students' skills and knowledge as they approach the end of compulsory education. It seems that PISA 2012 survey is about how well student is prepared for life beyond school rather than just how well student have observed school lessons. Around 510,000 students in 65 economies took part in the PISA 2012 assessment of reading, mathematics and science representing about 28 million 15-year-olds globally.

Qulaity and Tideness issues¶

Following quality issues I found for data wrangling process..

  • Florida (USA), Connecticut (USA), Massachusetts (USA) should be changed to USA and Perm(Russian Federation) to Russian Federation
  • Country's full names should be changed to three character code
  • ST07Q01, ST07Q02, ST07Q03 will be merged to one column as repeat_particpation. Most frequent one will be chosen.Then, delete the columns above.
  • ST11Q01 and ST11Q02 will be changed to 0 and 1, if it is nan change it to the 1
  • ST14Q01, ST14Q02, ST14Q03 and ST14Q04 merge tables to one column as mother_qualification. Most frequent one will be chosen. Then, delete the columns above
  • ST18Q01, ST18Q02, ST18Q03 and ST18Q04 merge tables to one column as father_qualification. Most frequent one will be chosen. Then, delete the columns above

Qulaity and Tideness issues¶

  • 'PV1MATH', 'PV2MATH', 'PV3MATH', 'PV4MATH', 'PV5MATH' - get the average value and delete columns
  • 'PV1READ', 'PV2READ', 'PV3READ', 'PV4READ', 'PV5READ' - get the average value and delete columns
  • 'PV1SCIE', 'PV2SCIE', 'PV3SCIE', 'PV4SCIE', 'PV5SCIE' - get the average value and delete columns
  • Work ethic common columns should be selected and melt to rows and count inside for heatmap

Univariate Exploration¶

The top 3 most frequent countries are Mexico, Italy and Spain. Next, I am going to discover the gender distribution of the pisa dataset. Because, I am also planning to explore if boy student study better than girl student or vice-versa.

Percentage of gender distribution is almost same. So, I can compare boys and girls without having simpson's paradox. Now, let's see if gender has imapct on average academic score of student's.

Average academic scores of both genders are almost same. However, If we look deeply, we can only see that reading for female is slightly higher than male and on the other hand, male are slightly betterr in mathematics than female. Next, I am going to determine Plausable average score dsitribution to determine, it the scores are normally distributed.

Wow, all the average score distributions are normally distributed. The peak for all academics between 420 and 460. Now, let's explore parent's info. We will start by working status.

More fathers' have full-time job than mothers. It seems mothers have more home duties than fathers. Unemployment rate is low for both of the genders which is very good. Now, let's check theit education level

The highest proportion for both gender corresponds to International Standard Classification of Education of level 3A which is upper secondary education. Next, let's determine birth country of parent's and self

It is obvious from above that, most of students are from country where PISA test happened(93% vs 7%).

We can see that for both father and mother who came as immigrant slightly higher than their children.

Most of the parents are from test country
